            BBC survey finds out what makes people happy
            A survey for the BBC suggests that the happiest people in Britain live in Yorkshire and East Anglia.  They say it is mainly because they have friendly communities and easy access to green spaces.   Apart from having more money, it seems our idea of happiness is sitting in front of the television eating pizza and chocolate.  Kevin Burch reports from Suffolk.
                
                        02 Nov 2010
                    
                
        
